                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>N. Y. Apr. 29th&#47;89<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Dr&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>I regret to state that it<lb/> will be impossible to convene the<lb/> Seminary classes at 2.30 P.M. on Wed&#45;<lb/>&#45;nesday as it is the greatest day of<lb/> the centennial celebration &#38; the Sem&#45;<lb/>&#45;inary students march with the<lb/> pupils of the city colleges &#38; schools<lb/> in the civic parade.  The streets<lb/> of the city are impassable from<lb/> morning to evening &#38; it would be<lb/> very inadvisable to call the classes<lb/> then.  Thursday at the same<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>hour would be a very good time.<lb/>  If you can come to N. Y. on Thurs&#45;<lb/>&#45;day please let me now by telegram<lb/> <hi rend="underline">at once</hi> &#38; I will call the classes<lb/> for them.  I have the honor to be<lb/> very truly yours<lb/> Bernard Drachman<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>From<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">329 E. 51<hi rend="sup">st</hi> St</hi><lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. S. Morais<lb/>
                546 North 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                Pa.<lb/></p>
            </body>
